&lt;p&gt;You sit upstream of the content engine — developing brand-level creative platforms, campaign concepts, and content systems that are rooted in insight and built for the feed. You partner closely with Social Producers to ensure that creative vision translates into best-in-class execution, and you work in close collaboration with Director-level creative leadership to connect your account-level work to broader brand and agency strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are platform-native, data-literate, and creatively ambitious. You see emerging formats before they hit culture, you can tell the difference between a trend and a fad, and you know that on social media, the most powerful creative is born at the intersection of instinct and insight. This role is designed for someone ready to own their accounts deeply — and grow into the cross-portfolio, team, and agency responsibilities that define the Director level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day-to-Day Scope:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Portfolio: 2–3 client accounts, balanced across client size and service mix to build depth across different brand challenges and content models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team: You will partner closely with Social Producers and cross-functional staff — serving as the creative strategic lead who translates ideation and conceptualization into clear, executable direction. You do not carry direct reports at this level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cadence: Always-on content programs with reactive moments and campaign work layered in. Your primary rhythm is strategic output — briefs, platforms, concepts, and frameworks — that keeps the production engine moving with creative purpose.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ownership: You own the creative strategy and conceptual quality for your assigned accounts, and the day-to-day creative relationship with those clients. Cross-portfolio creative vision and department-level creative leadership sit at the Director level and above.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
